TypeScript Form Project

Basic web form in TypeScript using the Express framework. When the form is submitted, the information is printed to the server console.

Project structure

Copy code
project-form/
├── src/
│ └── app.ts # Main server code in TypeScript
├── views/
│ └── form.html # HTML form
├── dist/ # TypeScript output folder (generated on build)
├── package.json # Configuration file for dependencies and scripts
└── tsconfig.json # TypeScript configuration
Prerequisites
Node.js (v14 or higher)
npm (Node.js package manager)
Installation
Clone the project or create a new folder.

attempt

Copy code
git clone <repository-url> project-form
cd project-form
Install dependencies .

attempt

Copy code
npm install
TypeScript Configuration
This project uses TypeScript and Express. The configuration is located in the tsconfig.json file and is ready to be compiled in the dist directory.

Running the project
To start the project, you have two options:

Development mode (auto-reload):

attempt

Copy code
npm run dev
Production mode :

attempt

Copy code
npm start
Using the project
Open the browser and navigate to http://localhost:3000 .
Fill out the form and submit it.
The submitted responses will be displayed in the server console.
Available Scripts
npm start: Builds the project and runs the compiled code in production.
npm run dev: Builds the project and runs the server in development mode with auto-reload (uses nodemon).
Customization
You can modify the views/form.html form to add or remove fields, and customize the handling of app.ts responses within the /submit path.
